rComments: Anja doesn't explain concepts well and doesn't provide any examples. There was no textbook so it was based on her lecture notes. She doesn't give any pity marks and the course is heavy with online quizzes, tutorial quizzes, problem set questions, midterm and final. I wish a more experienced prof would teach this course.
Ania is great. It's the first time in four years that I'm actually enjoying math!
Professor Randecker cares very much about the students and their mathematical education. Her demands are high, both from the students and from herself as an instructor. Nice professor!

The best prof I've had so far! She puts A LOT of efforts in making the materials clear. When she's teaching you can actually see the beauty of math! Her expectations fit well the teaching level, i.e. if you actually understand the lectures (go to her office hours - it is very helpful!), you shoudn't worry about your final grade.

She's nice, but incredibly new and with that it seems like she is following "the book" to a tee. Perhaps quite literally. Grading of tests and assignments are above and beyond strict, with little leeway for partial grades.

Very good instructor in teaching the course content, but unlike other mathematical theory based courses, she marks her exams very quickly and is quick to mark incorrect for any answer that is not exactly the same as her solution. I recommend memorizing the proofs exactly or you wont get full marks even if your proof is correct.
If you want to graduate with D or fail, just take it.
